<dl id="n12140i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12140i">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12140i"> 140(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> pretends to die</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Part of the <font color="green">[Australian initiation]</font> ritual includes <mark>a simulated death and reanimation</mark>. Among the Kurnai tribe of Australia, for instance, the boys, during the initiation ceremonies, were &ldquo;put to sleep&rdquo; at night, and woke the next day as men. <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 151</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12144e" href="c12all.htm#c12144e">VI.C.12:144(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
